provides: [range, stat, names, word]
---

# git diff

Compare two points in history (where @git/stage `diff` only covers the working
tree). `range` shows the full diff between refs; `stat` summarizes per file;
`names` lists just the changed paths (for scripting); `word` highlights changes
within a line. Refs and the `A..B` range grammar come from @git/refs;
@git/history shows the commits behind a range.

| Recipe | Flags | Shows |
|--------|-------|-------|
| `range` | — | full diff between two refs (or ref vs working tree) |
| `stat` | `--stat` | per-file insertion/deletion counts |
| `names` | `--name-only` | just the changed filenames |
| `word` | `--word-diff` | changes highlighted within each line |

`git diff main..feature` is "what feature changed relative to main"; a single
ref (`git diff main`) compares it to the working tree. `--name-only` feeds a
pipeline — `git diff --name-only main | xargs …` acts on changed files
(@search/xargs). `--stat` is the at-a-glance review; `--word-diff` shines on
prose or single-line edits where a line diff is noise. Add `-- path` to scope to
one file. `git diff --cached` is the staged diff (same as @git/stage `diff --staged`).

```just
# full diff between two refs, or a ref vs the working tree (default)
range a b="":
  git diff {{quote(a)}} {{b}}

# per-file insertion/deletion summary
stat a b="":
  git diff --stat {{quote(a)}} {{b}}

# just the changed filenames (for piping)
names a b="":
  git diff --name-only {{quote(a)}} {{b}}

# changes highlighted within each line (word-level)
word a b="":
  git diff --word-diff {{quote(a)}} {{b}}
```
